claim.claim-text:
1. A positron emission tomography apparatus comprising:
a bed on which a subject is to be laid;
an image pickup device that is provided with a plurality of semiconductor radiation detectors for detecting γ rays from said subject and a support member for supporting said semiconductor radiation detectors, said semiconductor radiation detectors being arranged in a plurality of layers and in a direction away from said bed on which said subject is to be placed, wherein γ rays passing through one of said semiconductor radiation detectors is detected by another of said semiconductor radiation detectors arranged in said direction away from said bed;
a signal processor connected to said plurality of semiconductor radiation detectors, for coincidence processing γ rays detection signals detected by said semiconductor radiation detectors;
wherein said signal processor comprises γ-ray signal processors, wherein each of said γ-ray signal processors connects to separate semiconductor radiation detectors which are arranged in each of said layers; and
a tomogram generator for creating tomogram data of said subject on the basis of positional information of said semiconductor radiation detectors representing an arrived position of a pair of coincidence processed γ rays in a direction away from said bed, said positional information being output information of said signal processor.

10. A positron emission tomography apparatus comprising:
a bed on which a medical examinee is to be laid;
an image pickup device that includes a plurality of semiconductor radiation detectors arranged so as to surround said bed for detecting γ rays from said medical examinee and a support member for supporting said semiconductor radiation detectors, said semiconductor radiation detectors being arranged in a plurality of layers and in a direction away from said bed;
a signal processor connected to said plurality of semiconductor radiation detectors, for coincidence processing γ rays detection signals detected by said semiconductor radiation detectors;
wherein said signal processor comprises γ-ray signal processors, wherein each of said γ-ray signal processors connects to separate semiconductor radiation detectors which are arranged in each of said layers; and
a tomogram generator for creating tomogram data of said medical examinee on the basis of positional information of said semiconductor detectors representing an arrived position of a pair of coincidence processed γ rays in a direction away from said bed, said positional information being output information of said signal processor.

17. The positron emission tomography apparatus according to claim 15, comprising a tomogram data generator;
wherein said signal processor connected to semiconductor radiation detectors located in some radiation detector layers that are positioned on a side nearest said bed include includes X-ray signal processors for outputting first information about X-rays in accordance with said first detection signal and γ-ray signal processors for outputting second information about γ-rays in accordance with said second detection signal, and wherein said signal processor connected to semiconductor radiation detectors located in the remaining semiconductor radiation detector layers of the multiple semiconductor radiation detector layers does not include said X-ray signal processors but include said γ-ray signal processors; and
wherein said tomogram data generator creates first tomogram data about said examinee in accordance with said first information that is output from said X-ray signal processors, creates second tomogram data about said examinee in accordance with said second information that is output from said γ-ray signal processors, and creates synthesized tomogram data by synthesizing said first tomogram data and said second tomogram data.

20. A radiological imaging apparatus comprising:
a bed on which a medical examinee is to be laid;
an image pickup device that includes a plurality of radiation detectors for detecting the radiation from said medical examinee, said radiation detectors being disposed in said image pickup device, arranged around the circumference of a through-hole into which said bed is to be inserted, and mounted at different positions in the radial direction of said through-hole; and signal processors that are each connected to corresponding one of said radiation detectors to process a radiation detection signal detected by said corresponding one of said radiation detectors;
a radiation detector deterioration check device;
wherein said plurality of radiation detectors are arranged in said direction of the radius to form multiple radiation detector layers, wherein said signal processors connected to said radiation detectors output first information upon input of a γ-ray detection signal, which is said radiation detection signal; and
wherein said radiation detector deterioration check device determines the measured detection efficiency proportion of radiation detectors in said multiple layers in accordance with said first information about the radiation detectors and uses the resultant measured value proportion and theoretical detection efficiency proportion of the radiation detectors to determine whether the radiation detectors are deteriorated.

21. A radiological imaging apparatus comprising:
a bed on which a medical examinee is to be laid;
an image pickup device that includes a plurality of semiconductor radiation detectors arranged so as to surround said bed for detecting radiation from said medical examinee and a support member for supporting said semiconductor radiation detectors, said semiconductor radiation detectors being mounted on a same side surface of said support member and arranged in a plurality of layers and in a direction away from said bed; and
a signal processor connected to said plurality of semiconductor radiation detectors, for processing radiation detection signals detected by said semiconductor radiation detectors;
a radiation detector deterioration check device;
wherein said plurality of semiconductor radiation detectors are arranged in said direction of the radius to form multiple radiation detector layers, wherein said signal processors connected to said semiconductor radiation detectors output first information upon input of a γ-ray detection signal, which is said radiation detection signal; and
wherein said radiation detector deterioration check device determines the measured detection efficiency proportion of semiconductor radiation detectors in said multiple layers in accordance with said first information about the semiconductor radiation detectors and uses the resultant measured value proportion and theoretical detection efficiency proportion of the semiconductor radiation detectors to determine whether the semiconductor radiation detectors are deteriorated.

22. A positron emission tomography apparatus comprising:
a bed for supporting a subject;
an image pickup device having a plurality of semiconductor detectors arranged so as to surround said bed for detecting γ rays from the subject and a support member for supporting said semiconductor detectors, each of said semiconductor detectors being arranged in a plurality of layers and in a direction away from said bed;
γ-ray signal processors, wherein each of said γ-ray signal processors connects to separate semiconductor radiation detectors which are arranged in each of said layers; and
a tomogram information generator for creating tomogram information of the subject on the basis of positional information representing an arrived position of a pair of coincidence processed γ rays in a direction away from said bed, said positional information being based on γ rays detecting signals, said γ rays detecting signals being detected by the semiconductor detectors arranged in said plurality of layers.

24. A method of inspecting a subject using positron emission tomography, comprising the steps of:
detecting γ rays from a subject by a plurality of semiconductor detectors arranged around a bed supporting said subject, each of said semiconductor detectors being arranged in a plurality of layers and in a direction away from said bed;
generating γ rays detection signals detected by said plurality of semiconductor detectors;
discriminating said γ rays detection signals by γ-ray discriminators, each of said γ-ray discriminators being connected to semiconductor detectors which are arranged in each of said layers;
coincidence processing said γ rays detection signals by a signal processor connected to said plurality of semiconductor detectors; and
creating tomogram information of said subject on the basis of positional information representing an arrived position of a pair of coincidence processed γ rays in a direction away from said bed, said positional information being detected by the semiconductor detectors arranged in said plurality of layers.

25. A method of imaging a subject using positron emission tomography, comprising:
detecting γ rays from a subject by a plurality of semiconductor detectors arranged around a bed supporting said subject, said semiconductor detectors being arranged in a plurality of layers and in a direction away from said bed;
generating γ rays detection signals detected by said plurality of semiconductor detectors;
discriminating said γ rays detection signals by y-ray discriminators, each of said γ-ray discriminators being connected to semiconductor detectors which are arranged in each of said layers;
coincidence processing said γ rays detection signals by a signal processor connected to said plurality of semiconductor detectors;
generating pulse signals in response to said γ ray detection signals, wherein each of said γ ray detection signals being detected by separate semiconductor radiation detectors which are arranged in each of said layers; and
creating tomogram information of said subject on the basis of positional information representing an arrived position of a pair of coincidence processed γ rays in a direction away from said bed, said positional information being detected by the semiconductor detectors arranged in said plurality of layers.
